{
  "texts": [
    "Requirement: These co-occurrences need to be objects or scenes in an indoor or outdoor environment that can be observed by the robot.",
    "Below you will find several examples of cooccurrences extraction and the target landmark, output by format: +bedroom example +sink example Tell me 10 cooccurrences of pillar: 1. column 2. statue 3. arch 4. staircase 5. balcony traction, we give the visualization examples of landmark extraction comparison among different methods in Fig. 7.From Fig.",
    "7, we can find that: (1) ChatGPT performs the best generally among all compared models; (2) Vicuna13B [58] is comparable to ChatGPT while sometimes extracting wrong navigational order; (3) Vicuna7B [58] also suffers from wrong navigational order (e.g., in Fig. 7(a), Vicuna7B extracts the \"stone tiles\" before extracting the \"wodden floor\"); (4) GPT-3 [17] is slightly inferior to ChatGPT for fine-grained landmark extraction (e.g., in Fig.",
    "7(a), GPT-3 extracts the \"wall\" and the \"fireplace\" rather than extracting the \"wall containing fireplace\"); ( 5) Spacy [59] can only extract the textual order rather than the navigational order and extracts a lot of noise (e.g., in Fig. 7(b), Spacy extracts the \"right\", the \"rest\", and the \"base\").",
    "These landmark extraction visualization results reveal the great potential of utilizing LLMs for assisting VLN."
  ]
}